Problem 1: Search X in Sorted Array
Source: takeuforward â€” https: // takeuforward. org/ plus/ dsa/ problems/

search-x-in-sorted-array Given a sorted array of integers and a target value X, de-
termine whether X exists in the array. If it exists, return its index (0-based). If it does

not exist, return -1.
Input: First line contains n, the size of array. Second line contains n integers. Third line
contains integer X.
Output: Single integer: index of X or -1.
Example
Input:
5
1 3 5 7 9
5
Output: 2
ANS:#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int n;
    cin >> n;

    int arr[n];
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> arr[i];
    }

    int x;
    cin >> x;

    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if(arr[i] == x) {
            cout << i;
            return 0;
        }
    }

    cout << -1;
    return 0;
}
